
[1]butcher-bird

   BUTCH'ER-BIRD, n. The shrike; a genus of birds, called Lanius. One
   species of this genus is called king-bird, from its courage in
   attacking hawks and crows.

   The king-bird is now arranged under the genus Muscicapa.
